Dear Mennix,<br><br>As a wood-elf ranger I have very deeply ingrained beliefs.  Some of those include an absolute hatred towards trolls, ogres, dark elves, and particularly necromancers, who befoul Norrath with their evil ways. The problem, however, is this, I occasionally run into an ogre or troll, not a dark elf, who is somewhat civilized and shares many beliefs with me.<br><br>This has forced me to question the ideals I have been taught since childhood, namely that those races deemed evil by the Elders, are evil and ought to be eradicated.<br><br>I did not place myself in this predicament on purpose.  I was busy attempting to clear the lands of the aptly named Lake of Ill-Omen, allowing for expansion from Firiona Vie and the eventual destruction of the Iksar as a race, who continue to land on the shores of Faydwer, when I found myself, though I hate to admit it, being bettered by what seemed to be an Iksar monk.  Just as I was about to utilize some of my magic to effect an escape, a large Ogre warrior ran up and aided me in the slaying of the monster.<br><br>Consequently, I did not attempt to slay him instantly. Not only was I badly injured, but he had just saved my life.  I have since had similar experiences with Trolls. What do I do?  Do I treat each troll and ogre as a separate case and go against the Elder's teachings, or do I slay them, killing allies against the Iksar?<br><br>Cermaz Zer'Terah<br>Champion of the Faydark<br><br><b>Dear Cermaz,<br><br>There is good reason to be distrustful of the darker races. They all are creatures born of evil. Regardless what some may say, this is a fact. The very gods of Norrath made it so. Your elders are correct in teaching you to see them as enemies. But, as evil can lurk within the hearts of all sentient beings, so can good lurk within a heart of the foulest beast. Yeah, yeah. I know that someone will call me on this since I seem to contradict myself from previous letters. Oh well. I am who I am.<br><br>Remember though, wisdom does not allow one to pass judgment on another due to the actions of a race. Each individual should be judged as an individual, regardless of what was taught to you by your elders. Trust your elders, but also trust yourself. <br><br>Do not take my words as permission to let your guard down when facing an individual of historical evil intent. And, always remember evil can smile too. Use your best judgment and let your conscience be your guide.</b><br><br><br>
