Dear Mennix,<br><br>I have noticed in my brief travels of Norrath a perplexing issue. Every day as I travel, helping others and ridding the lands of evil beasts and the undead, I hear many shouts of offers of teleports, SoW's, and other services. Normally such offers of community service would warm the heart of this young Paladin, but alas, it doesn't. Mennix, every time I hear these offers it is usually follow by a request for a donation. Now, when the crier is announcing "SoW’ing at the gate, donations accepted but not required!".... this seems acceptable. However, what I normally hear is more of this... "SoW’ing at the gate for donations!" It was always my teaching in the Temple of Marr and the Hall of Truth that donations were something that you free give and not a payment for a service. I have never stopped and asked someone that was yelling for help if they would make a donation first. I have never asked for a single copper for any heal, escort, cure, or other service that I have performed. Granted, only once has anyone offered a tribute to the awesome power of Mithaniel Marr, but I feel that this only strengthens my loyalty to my chosen path. Can you help this young Paladin understand why so many out there try to hide their greed behind a veil accepting a donation?<br><br>Dondelde<br>Loyal Paladin of Mithaniel Marr, Veeshan<br><br><br><b>Dear Dondelde,<br><br>Should all services be rendered for free? Some people do have to make a living. Granted, it would be nice if everything in life came without a price tag, but I will never belittle another for trying to generate an income. <br><br>Would it be better if a seller set a firm price and did not ask for a donation instead? Maybe. I don’t rightly know. Each seller has the right to determine how they will peddle their product. With a donation at least, a buyer can still obtain a service at a much lower fee. If services are rendered for free, great! I commend those such as yourself who do first for your god and your income second. It shows dedication to a belief. Just don’t forget, everyone does not have the same beliefs or faith. Oh, and one more thing, a seller has no way to force a buyer to purchase his or her product with either a donation or a set selling price.<br><br>Let those who seek profit seek it. If you don’t know their motivations for doing so, don’t automatically assume it’s because of greed.</b> <br>
